The Second Moment Approximation (SMA) model potential is a many-body potential that approximates the local environment of every atom mimicking the distribution of electronic states in a d-band by a bonding term Uel, supplemented with the Urep Born-Mayer term for the short-range repulsion8. The SMA is a classical version of the tight-binding approach. As such, the SMA differs significantly from pair-additive classical models and has a characteristic very soft spheres repulsive wall. The SMA analytical expression is a sum, Ucoh = Urep + Uel, with1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
